  "signature": "ed25519:b2c3d4e5f6a7b8c9d0e1f2a3b4c5d6e7f8a9b0c1d2e3f4a5b6c7d8e9f0a1b2c3",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022 R1) with documented release notes; internal SQA checklist completed per ISO 9001 procedures; simulation input files archived in Git repository with SHA-1 hashes recorded.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022 R1 is a commercially validated solver with documented SQA processes meeting Gradation 2 requirements. All simulation scripts and case files are version-controlled under the project Git repository. Release notes and patch documentation are on file. Internal SQA checklist (Form SQA-CFD-07) was completed by the lead analyst and reviewed by the project quality engineer."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes published benchmark cases (lid-driven cavity Re=1000, Poiseuille flow) with L2 error norms below 1e-4; documented in ANSYS verification manual and confirmed by in-house replication.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent has been verified against standard benchmark cases including the lid-driven cavity at Re=1000 and fully developed Poiseuille flow. The in-house replication of both benchmarks produced L2 velocity error norms of 8.3e-5 and 6.1e-5 respectively, satisfying the stated acceptance threshold. Results are archived in the project verification report (VVR-NCV-001)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid Convergence Index (GCI) for the primary QoI (volume-averaged shear stress) must be below 5% on the medium mesh used for production runs; Richardson extrapolation performed on three systematically refined meshes.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted using coarse (2.1M cells), medium (5.8M cells), and fine (14.2M cells) hexahedral-dominant meshes. Richardson extrapolation yielded a GCI of 2.7% for volume-averaged shear stress on the medium mesh, well within the 5% threshold. The apparent order of convergence was 1.94, consistent with the second-order spatial discretization scheme employed. The medium mesh was selected for all production runs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow rates, rotational speeds, fluid temperature) must be reproduced in CFD boundary conditions within ±2% of measured values; documented mapping table required.",
      "rationale": "All five experimental operating points were replicated in the CFD model with inlet flow rates and impeller rotational speeds matched to within 1.1% of the experimentally recorded values. Fluid temperature was held at 37°C ± 0.5°C in both experiment and simulation. The boundary condition mapping table (Table BC-01 in the validation report) documents the correspondence between experimental measurements and CFD inputs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) must agree with experimental measurements within ±15% across all five operating points; systematic bias must be below 5%.",
      "rationale": "Predicted RH values across all five operating points fell within ±11.3% of experimental measurements, satisfying the ±15% agreement criterion. Mean signed error was +3.8%, below the 5% systematic bias threshold. The model consistently slightly over-predicts hemolysis, which is conservative for the intended regulatory use. Detailed comparison plots are provided in validation report section 4.3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The validated QoI (volume-averaged shear stress and derived RH index) must be directly traceable to the regulatory submission QoI; traceability matrix required.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI used in validation (relative hemolysis index computed from volume-averaged shear stress via the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model) is identical to the QoI specified in the regulatory submission protocol. The traceability matrix (Appendix A of the credibility assessment report) maps each validation QoI to its corresponding submission requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "The validation activities were conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry — the same geometry class as the device under assessment — operating across the full clinical flow-speed envelope (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). Blood analogue fluid (40% glycerol-water, viscosity matched to whole blood at 37°C) was used in the experimental campaign. The operating Reynolds number range in validation experiments (Re = 1800–4200) brackets the COU operating range (Re = 2100–3900), ensuring that the validation domain is not extrapolated beyond the COU. Geometric fidelity between the validation and COU configurations was confirmed by dimensional inspection report DIM-2023-07. The combination of matched fluid rheology, overlapping operating envelope, and identical pump geometry class provides strong evidence that the validation activities are directly relevant to the COU. No significant gaps in relevance were identified that would require additional validation activities at MRL 2. The turbulence model sensitivity study further confirmed that model-form uncertainty is bounded within the accepted QoI tolerance across the full operating envelope relevant to the COU."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor; scoped out per Table 3 of the credibility assessment plan.",
      "rationale": "Per ASME V&V 40 Table 3, numerical solver error is not required to be assessed at Model Risk Level 2 when software quality assurance and numerical code verification have been addressed. This factor is scoped out of the current assessment."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; analyst qualification records maintained separately per SOPs.",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment is not required at MRL 2 for this device class. Analyst qualifications and simulation execution checklists are maintained under the quality management system but formal use error assessment is deferred per the credibility assessment plan."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; turbulence model selection rationale documented in simulation plan.",
      "rationale": "Formal model form assessment is not required at MRL 2. The turbulence model sensitivity study (SST k-omega vs. realizable k-epsilon) was conducted as a supplementary activity and confirmed that QoI sensitivity to turbulence model selection is below 8% across all operating points, providing informal evidence of model form adequacy."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; input parameter ranges documented in simulation plan section 2.4.",
      "rationale": "Formal model input uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2. Key material properties (blood viscosity, density) and boundary condition uncertainties are documented in the simulation plan. Sensitivity of RH to ±5% variation in viscosity was evaluated informally and found to produce less than 3% change in predicted RH."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; experimental sample documentation provided by testing laboratory.",
      "rationale": "Formal test sample characterization is not required at MRL 2. The experimental data used for validation was obtained from a single pump unit tested at an accredited laboratory. Unit-to-unit variability was not assessed but is considered acceptable given the precision manufacturing tolerances of the FDA generic pump geometry."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; parameter equivalency addressed qualitatively in the credibility assessment report.",
      "rationale": "Equivalency of input parameters between the validation configuration and the COU is addressed qualitatively. The blood analogue fluid properties were matched to within 3% of whole blood at 37°C. Geometric equivalency was confirmed by dimensional inspection. No formal parameter equivalency assessment is required at MRL 2."
    }
  ],
